Do a global search for non-whitespace characters in a string:

Copy
let str = "Is this all there is?";
let patt1 = /\S/g;
let result = str.match(patt1);
console.log(result);
Output:


Description
The \S metacharacter can find a non-whitespace character.

A whitespace character can be:

A space character
A tab character
A carriage return character
A new line character
A vertical tab character
A form feed character
Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
\S	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
new RegExp("\\S") or simply: /\S/
Syntax with modifiers
Copy
new RegExp("\\S", "g") or simply: /\S/g
